<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-12-13T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-12-13T10:00:00-05:00" n="549" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d549">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 Lithuania/93:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Lithuania (<persName type="from">Stafford</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kaunas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-12-13T16:00:00+01:00">December 13, 1932—4 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received December 13—11:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>22. Minister for Foreign Affairs informs me despite request for
                                revision or postponement preparations for payment of interest due on
                                the 15 being made. Whether payment will be unconditional will depend
                                upon action of other debtors particularly France.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stafford</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>